programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Baby giraffe Jule is giving her keeper the runaround, while hand-reared capuchin monkey Sina just wants her family to accept her. Young Akili has her first trip outside the rhino enclosure.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: The hippos enjoy a cooling swim in their Olympic-size pool. Meanwhile, the keepers search for an orphaned aardvark born during the night.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Some animals take longer than others to learn the rules of zoo life — the young elephants prove particularly mischievous. Meanwhile, the capybara pups give their keepers a tough time.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Zoo Juniors need to be independent, but they also need to obey the rules. In Berlin, the baby elephants continue their rebellious streak.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Two newborn giraffes make trouble when they go outside together, so one must remain indoors. Meanwhile, the tamarins welcome their latest offspring to the troupe.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Climbing trees is second nature to the black bear cubs, but their antics make their keepers nervous. The hippos enjoy an afternoon snack in the pool while Evita the anteater is bottle fed.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: For many species, play is a big part of growing up. In Berlin, the dingo family plays rough. Meanwhile, Zamuco the peccary pig and Xena the Diana monkey get some personalized attention.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Zoo Juniors come in all shapes and sizes, from the zoo’s rare Chinese leopard twins to the Animal Park’s shy okapi infant.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: The langurs always attract visitors with their beautiful orange fur. Leopard cub Timang has a big personality for such a tiny cat. Xena the Diana monkey gets to go home with her keeper.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Zoo Juniors enjoy first-class meals and personal service. Zamuco is bottle fed in the keepers' staff room. Meanwhile, the hippos get an enormous swimming pool all to themselves.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Zookeeper Angelika's hands are full with two Asian leopard species and a North American puma. It’s just as busy in the giraffe house, which recently became home to a newborn calf.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Wild animals are sometimes rejected at birth. But here in Berlin, any Zoo Junior abandoned by its parents always has a favorite keeper to rely on, like Sina the capuchin monkey.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: In Berlin, capybara pups cause trouble in the zoo's pond. Meanwhile, the llamas and alpacas play in the park while visitors look on.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Often, the zookeepers must care for animals that have been rejected at birth. Today, they bottle-feed a rare Chacoan peccary and twin goats.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: One giraffe gives birth in the outdoor enclosure while another takes his first walk in the paddock. In the big cat house, zookeepers weigh three bearcat kittens.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: While one Asian elephant celebrates her birthday, another has an urgent visit from the dentist. Meanwhile, there’s a surprise arrival all the way from South America.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: New Zoo Juniors are arriving all the time. The keepers introduce the Javan leopard cub Pelangi, the black rhinos’ latest calves and Opala's tiny baby.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Okapis from Central Africa celebrate a birthday while Australian emus enjoy their first day outdoors. The Madagascan lemurs have a new baby, but they're not letting anyone get close.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Whether they’re from blistering deserts or the freezing cold Himalayas, our Juniors are learning how to fit in at the zoo. The snow leopard twins get their final inoculations and their names.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: From the Sahara Desert to the open grasslands, today's Zoo Juniors all come from Africa. The queen mole rat is giving birth to a brood and the springhares have had a successful season.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Things are very busy at the big cat house. Zookeeper Angelika hand-rears Siberian tiger cub Alisha while her colleague Petra looks after nine-week-old quadruplets.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: The ape house at the zoo has a new arrival: orangutan baby Rieke. She was rejected by her mother and relies totally on her keeper for her care, much like newborn orphan armadillo Oleg.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Today's animals are all very hungry. Milk is no longer sufficient for Rhea the Diana monkey; she is weaning and moving on to solid foods. Wallaby orphan Monti is taking his time with his milk bottle.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: At three months old, tiger cub Alisha needs to play with her own kind. Sister Diana monkeys Rhea and Xena are introduced for the first time.

programme.title: Zoo Juniors
programme.desc: Long before the other Zoo Juniors awake, orangutan baby Rieke heads to the airport for the journey of a lifetime.

programme.title: Countdown to Catastrophe: Volcanoes
programme.desc: Mount Nyiragongo stands an altitude of 3500 meters with lava that boils at 1000.

programme.title: Countdown to Catastrophe: Earthquakes
programme.desc: In many countries of the world people are so used to earthquakes that a little jolt of the ground barely raises an eyebrow. But since the Fukushima nuclear reactor disaster the issue of seismic security has taken on new urgency.

programme.title: Countdown to Catastrophe: Storms
programme.desc: What impact do hurricanes make on the global climate? Geophysicist Shimon Wdowinski from the University of Miami has discovered a truly astonishing connection: major storms can trigger massive earthquakes.

programme.title: Death on the Matterhorn
programme.desc: Seven men stand on the summit of the Matterhorn, the last Alpine peak to be conquered. Their place in history is assured. Then, disaster strikes: a rope snaps. Four men die. But did the rope really just snap...or was it cut?

programme.title: Mont Saint-Michel: Resistance Through the Ages
programme.desc: Mont Saint-Michel has stood in the middle of a vast bay off the French coast of Normandy for centuries. It has become a symbol of resistance to the test of time. This film offers a journey through the history and mysteries of this indomitable fortress.

programme.title: Human Prey: Deadly Waters
programme.desc: While on the job at an Florida golf club, an experienced golf ball diver is attacked by a territorial, 400-pound alligator. Jeff Tanswell's snorkeling trip turns into a bloody battle for his life when he is dragged under by an 12-foot saltwater crocodile.

programme.title: Human Prey: Killer Canines and Felines
programme.desc: On a camping trip in the Canadian wilderness, a family is unwittingly stalked by a hungry and opportunistic wolf. A mountain bike excursion in California becomes a life-and-death struggle when a cyclist is pounced and attacked upon by a 110 pound cougar.

programme.title: Human Prey: Killer Sharks
programme.desc: While diving for shellfish off Cape Howe, an Australian man ends up inside the jaws of a Great White shark. Determined to maintain his championship spear fishing title, an Australian man inadvertently becomes bait for a 15-foot-long Great White shark.

programme.title: Germany's Underworld: From the Alps to the River Rhine
programme.desc: This is a journey through Germany’s rivers, streams and lakes, from the snow-clad peaks of the Alps to the River Rhine. The force of the water creates wondrous ice caves, spectacular waterfalls and extraordinary turquoise lakes.

programme.title: Germany's Underworld: From the Harz Mountain to the North Sea
programme.desc: We follow the migration of an ancient fish, the Atlantic sturgeon, and meet hunters, like the ground beetle and the sea eagle. On the banks of the river, a family of beavers explore the surroundings around their underwater lodge.

programme.title: Inside JFK's Assassination
programme.desc: A bodyguard, a photographer, a bystander, and the future widow of the President: on 22 November 1963, they were all in Dallas, and JFK’s assassination would forever be embedded in their memory. Relive that fateful day through their eyes.

programme.title: JFK's Women: The Scandals Revealed
programme.desc: John F. Kennedy, the charismatic president. However, with all that charm came a hidden life of reckless sexual adventure. He had a confirmed affair with Marilyn Monroe, and at least five of his endeavors posed a potential threat to national security.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Tent City Jail, Phoenix, Arizona, USA
programme.desc: Old army tents left over from the Korean War house prisoners instead of cells. The Sheriff is a hard man who refuses to spend any more than he has to on his prisoners. Harassment and humiliation is a part of everyday life at Tent City.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Antanimora Prison, Madagascar
programme.desc: Desperate overcrowding, rats, and disease come standard in Antanimora Prison. Surrounded by the capital Antananarivo, it's bursting at the seams. It was originally built for 800 prisoners, but now it contains more than 3,000 prisoners.

programme.title: Unicorn City
programme.desc: To prove leadership skills to a potential employer, Voss, a hardcore gamer entices his gamer buddies to create a utopia, but paradise is disrupted when his former nemesis and guild master decides to wage war for the city and the heart of Voss’ true love.

programme.title: Christmas Angel
programme.desc: Christmas wishes made before a long-abandoned house that start coming true lead an elementary schoolgirl to discover a reclusive woman living inside.

programme.title: Heaven Sent
programme.desc: Maire prays that her husband find the strength to let go of their 9 year marriage. Billy is asking that his wife receive the strength and wisdom to hold on. A 8-year-old runaway from heaven takes it upon herself to rekindle the romance that slipped away.

programme.title: Not Another Happy Ending
programme.desc: When a troubled editor discovers that his only successful author is blocked, he knows that he needs to do something about it. Starring: Karen Gillan, Stanley Weber, Iain De Caestecker, Gary Lewis.

programme.title: Finding Mrs. Claus
programme.desc: When Mrs. Claus (Mira Sorvino) feels neglected by her less than attentive husband (Will Sasso), she goes to Las Vegas to help a little girl with her Christmas wish.

programme.title: 6 Below
programme.desc: An adrenaline seeking snowboarder gets lost in a massive winter storm in the back country of the High Sierras. Starring: Josh Hartnett, Mira Sorvino, Sarah Dumont. It is based on the book Crystal Clear by Eric LeMarque and Davin Seay.

programme.title: Christmas in Wonderland
programme.desc: Starring Matthew Knight and Chris Kattan. Three children and their father move from California to Canada. When they go shopping at the mall, they find counterfeit cash, inadvertently help catch crooks, and make a discovery about Santa.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: High Wired

programme.desc: Jump from one moving boat to another. Climb into a fishing boat tank filled with dead squid and retrieve weights from the bottom. Contestants shimmy out on a flag pole that is approximately 20 feet from the building, free the flag and shimmy back.

programme.title: Fear Factor: Helicopter Fire Drill/Eat Rectum/Walking The Ledge
programme.desc: Players climb out over the skid and underneath the helicopter. Contestants shoot at target, determining the number of boiled pig rectums they will have to eat. Contestants must navigate around the ledge of a tall building.

programme.title: Fear Factor: Tight Rope/Flies/Ice Swim Part 1
programme.desc: Playmates Super Bowl Special Part 1.

programme.title: Fear Factor: Tight Rope/Flies/Ice Swim Part 2
programme.desc: Playmates Super Bowl Special Part 2.

programme.title: Fear Factor: Blimp Ladder Climb/Bobbing for Chicken Feet In A Barrel of Warxworms/Car Rollover
programme.desc: Contestants bob in plexiglass box of waxworms. A player also climbs out of a blimp and onto a rope ladder.

programme.title: Fear Factor: Helicopter Climb/Blender of Fear/Pole Hopper
programme.desc: Climb a rope ladder into a helicopter. Eat the blended concoction you are given. Move flags from the first to the last pole.

programme.title: Fear Factor: Vertical Gauntlet/Rat Hat/Semi-Truck Rope Walk
programme.desc: To run through a vertical obstacle course. Contestants will put their head inside the box with 24 rats. To cross a plank suspend between to speeding semi-trucks.

programme.title: Fear Factor: Window Walk/Coffin of Creatures/Submerged Cage Escape
programme.desc: Celebrity 2. To move flags from one open window across and around the outside of a building. To separate and move white snakes out of a group of green. To escape from a submerged cage and swim to a life ring.

programme.title: Fear Factor: Bridge Hang/Uterus Skee-Ball/Cable Plate Walk
programme.desc: To hang from a bridge. To eat Pig Uterus in the allotted time. To walk on suspended plates.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Arnie Calls It
programme.desc: While training waterbomber captains for the upcoming fire-fighting season, Chief Pilot Arnie makes a surprising decision. AJ becomes a DC-4 captain and ponders whether to accept a promotion.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Under New Management
programme.desc: Joe hires outsider Duane Hicks to help Buffalo navigate the future and coach Mikey. Gord and Sean's DC-3 delivery mission to the High Arctic goes awry when blizzard conditions and a broken oil cooler force an emergency landing.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Dambusters
programme.desc: Buffalo gets into the stunt flying business when veteran pilot Arnie flies the DC-4 for the re- enactment scene of a famous WWII bombing raid. A routine C-46 flight becomes dangerous when a hole in the plane's aging exhaust system sets off the fire alarm.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Chuck Walks
programme.desc: Critical of the many stops and starts in the Electra program, and frustrated with the constant drama at Buffalo, Chuck quits. Joe clashes with the maintenance department when a series of delays puts the sale of an old Canso waterbomber in jeopardy.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Gear Up, Gear Down
programme.desc: Frustrated with her lack of flying and stuck in a rut as a courier driver, Audrey decides her time at Buffalo is over. Devan, Ian and Jimmy deal with a hydraulic fluid leak in the C-46 on the valley run.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Big Boost
programme.desc: When a ferry breakdown causes a gasoline shortage, Duane begs Chuck to return and prepare the Electra for a fuel haul. Cory leads a rescue mission to retrieve an abandoned C-46 and Mikey escapes to Ottawa for a birthday joyride in a fighter jet.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Power Struggle
programme.desc: Duane lands a huge contract for the Electra and puts enormous pressure on mechanic Adam to prep the plane without the help of his mentor Chuck. Kelly plans her Mexican wedding, but Jynelle's sudden resignation leaves her in the lurch.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Top of the World
programme.desc: The Electra flies to Alert, the northernmost settlement on Earth, forcing Adam and Duane to work things out. Hay River rampie Tyler is on the fast track to a co-pilot seat, but first has to prove his flying ability to Buffalo's new chief pilot, Justin.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Last Days
programme.desc: Sparks fly when Joe discovers Gord has taken a job with a rival airline after completing expensive training on one of the Buffalo planes. Larry, a rookie rampie, makes a near fatal error while training on the C-46.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Push Comes to Shove
programme.desc: Trying to make his mark at Buffalo, Duane lands two more Electra contracts. But his over- zealous efforts result in a clash with the crew and with Joe, and a down-to-the-wire midnight departure to meet a deadline.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: The Doghouse
programme.desc: Duane's decision to leave the Electra crew unsupervised while he spends time at home jeopardizes the completion of a major contract. Young DC-3 co-pilot Graeme sees his chance to move up to a bigger plane disappear when he falls out of favour with Joe.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Ice Strip
programme.desc: Mechanic Jimmy is sent to a northern mining camp to create an ice landing strip on a remote lake where AJ will have to land a DC-3 and the much bigger C-46. New co-pilot Tyler faces the ultimate test - flying the sked with Joe.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Expect the Unexpected
programme.desc: Engine troubles on the C-46 during the valley run force Devan to shut down an engine. High winds wreak havoc for Devan and his crew on another C-46 mission to help clean up an oil spill in the Northwest Territories.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Coming Home
programme.desc: Rookie waterbomber pilot Scott gets his first taste of action when Buffalo responds to an emergency callout to fight fires in Alberta. Mikey and Rod think they hit the jackpot when they buy a million dollar firefighting plane on eBay at a bargain price.

programme.title: Ice Pilots: Dark Skies
programme.desc: When Yellowknife and the northern aviation community are rocked by three crashes within a month, Joe places an extra emphasis on safety, which is why he only trusts himself to perform a dangerous-looking DC-3 stunt landing for a visiting film crew.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Surely, You Jest, Part 2
programme.desc: Carly sets out hoping to uncover the mystery behind the Crimson Dragon, but after digging up some damaging dirt on the Arcadia Movement, she soon finds herself squaring off in a psychic duel with Sayer.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Spider, Part 1
programme.desc: Sayer signs up for a Shadow Duel against a Dark Signer who's out for revenge while Akiza agrees to battle a dark and sinister supermodel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Spider, Part 2
programme.desc: As the Dark Signer double duel draws to a climactic close, Carly and Misty unfold a catastrophic card combo that could send Akiza and Sayer to the Netherworld forever.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Monkey, Part 1
programme.desc: After Akiza falls into a state of unconsciousness, her father turns to Yusei in a last ditch effort to wake his beloved daughter from her catatonic condition.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Monkey, Part 2
programme.desc: As the battle between Signers presses on, Yusei turns to his trusty Stardust Dragon in an effort to keep the power of Akiza's Black Rose Dragon at bay.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Monkey, Part 3
programme.desc: With Yusei, Jack, Akiza and Luna all gathered together, Director Goodwin seizes the moment and decides to shed some light on the dark and formidable foes the four Signers will soon be battling.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mark of the Monkey, Part 4
programme.desc: In an effort to rid the Satellite Sector of the Dark Signers, Crow ventures out and challenges a sinister looking sneak to a duel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Whale of a Ride, Part 1
programme.desc: Crow challenges the newest member of the Dark Signers to a Turbo Duel, but before Crow's Blackwings can even take flight, his opponent unleashes an aerial assault of his own.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Whale of a Ride, Part 2
programme.desc: As the sky-high battle between Crow and Greiger heats up, Crow looks to elevate his game in order to ground Greiger's aerial attacks before they send him to the Netherworld forever.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Whale of a Ride, Part 3
programme.desc: With his life points on the line, Crow turns to his feathered friends in a last ditch effort to take out Greiger's Earthbound Immortal. Can Crow and his Blackwing's rise to the occasion?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Score to Settle, Part 1
programme.desc: Haunted by the memories of his last battle with Kalin, Yusei looks to bury the past by agreeing to duel his former friend in a rematch. Can Yusei defeat Kalin and seal the tower that this Dark Signer is guarding?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Score to Settle, Part 2
programme.desc: As the rematch between Kalin and Yusei continues, Yusei must find a way to out-think and out-maneuver the dark power of Kalin's Earthbound Immortal before it sends him to the Netherworld forever.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Destiny's Will, Part 1
programme.desc: Roman challenges Yusei to a Shadow Duel at the site of the original Ener-D Reactor. Meanwhile, Director Goodwin decides to make an unexpected visit to the Satellite Sector to settle some unfinished business he has with his Dark Signer brother.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Destiny's Will, Part 2
programme.desc: As the battle between Yusei and Roman rages on, Roman takes a time out to reveal the truth behind the original Ener-D Reactor's meltdown and the role Yusei's father played.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Shadows of Doubt, Part 1
programme.desc: Jack agrees to Turbo Duel Carly in an effort to defeat the darkness that has taken control of her. Can Jack rid the evil that has come to possess this one-time roving reporter?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Shadows of Doubt, Part 2
programme.desc: Jack kicks his duel into overdrive and summons his Red Dragon Archfiend in a desperate attempt to free Carly from the Dark Signers' control.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Truth and Consequences, Part 1
programme.desc: Hoping to finally find out the whereabouts of her long-lost brother, Misty challenges Akiza to a Shadow Duel in a maze of mirrors.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Truth and Consequences, Part 2
programme.desc: After unlocking Akiza's psychic powers, Sayer sets his sights on using them to get even with the Dark Signers for destroying the Arcadia Movement.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Signs of Doom, Part 1
programme.desc: Yusei, Jack and Crow face off against Goodwin in the ultimate Shadow Duel showdown.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Signs of Doom, Part 2
programme.desc: With the safety of the world hanging in the balance, Yusei, Jack and Crow look to tip the scales in their favor by setting their sights on Goodwin's Earthbound Immortal.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Signs of Doom, Part 3
programme.desc: With his life points running on empty, Yusei looks to rev it up one last time in order to defeat Goodwin and save the world from the destructive powers of the King of the Netherworld!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A New Threat: Part I
programme.desc: A mysterious new threat arrives on the scene in New Domino City, forcing Yusei to take to the streets and track down a rogue Turbo Duelist known as The Ghost.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's
programme.desc: With his life points on the line, Yusei must figure out a way to take down Ghost's Meklord Emperor Wisel before Wisel's special ability throws his game and his runner into a tailspin.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Lessons Learned
programme.desc: When Vice Chancellor Rudolph Heitmann threatens to expel all the members of Leo and Luna's class from Duel Academy, Yusei attempts to teach the teacher a valuable lesson by challenging the Vice Chancellor to a duel to keep his friends in school.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Trash Talk
programme.desc: When Crow is asked to convince an old friend of Martha's to move into her retirement home, Crow decides to tackle the task by challenging the old man to a trash-talking junkyard duel. Can Crow convince the old man to relocate?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: A Duel with Interest
programme.desc: When a loan shark starts sinking his teeth into New Domino City, Jack decides to reel in this money-grubbing menace for good by putting his most prized possessions on the line in a duel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Wicked Spirits
programme.desc: When Leo and Luna decide to go exploring a nearby forest rumored to be haunted by wicked spirits, they soon discover that the rumors are all too real when a mysterious boy traps Luna in his house and challenges Leo to a duel.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: French Twist: Part I
programme.desc: Yusei wakes up to find himself trapped in the back of a big rig with a bump on his head and no way out. After a mysterious tip leads Akiza to Yusei's location, the two friends soon find themselves Turbo Dueling an unfamiliar foe.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: French Twist: Part II
programme.desc: As the battle between Yusei and Sherry races on, Sherry reveals some shocking secrets about the upcoming World Racing Grand Prix. Meanwhile, Akiza begins to gain a new understanding and appreciation for Turbo Dueling while riding shotgun to Yusei.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Synchro Straits
programme.desc: Before heading out to the event of the year - The World Racing Grand Prix Gala - Yusei challenges Jack to a Turbo Duel in the hopes of finding a new dueling strategy that doesn't involve the use of Synchro Monsters.

programme.title: Superhero Man
programme.desc: Spurned by his lover by the rich and successful 'Wayne Bruce,' a man becomes a superhero villain to get his revenge on this good guy. He recruits some henchmen to help him pull off the job, with hilarious results.

programme.title: Izzie's Way Home

programme.desc: When a colossal tectonic shift causes the sea level to start rising, a microbiologist gathers the DNA of as many species as she can, while the military creates an "ark" in a desperate attempt to preserve life on Earth.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension's Bex and Sean travel to Knutsford, Cheshire and visit the Legh Arms.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: A 16th Century pub that has a haunted history. The duo come into direct contact with spirits haunting the location. Even during the day there is no shortage of ghostly activity, on this lock down special paranormal Ghost Dimension investigation.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: The duo come into direct contact with spirits haunting the location. Even during the day there is no shortage of ghostly activity, on this lock down special paranormal Ghost Dimension investigation.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: Many urban explorers have encountered paranormal activity inside of the building, including child like figures, unexplained voices and strange knocking sounds. Will anything from the ghost dimension make contact?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension's Bex and Sean investigate Norris Green Mansion. A 17th Century building, which is believed to hold some of the most haunted spirits in Liverpool. Will they make contact its ghostly entities tonight?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension Lockdown
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension's Bex and Sean head to New Mills and investigate a home situated on the grounds of death and destruction from the bombings of WW2. Will any of the spirits lost in this disaster come forward and make contact during the investigation today?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Ghosts of Bolton Sea Cadets
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team heads to Bolton to check out the alleged haunting at Sea Cadets academy.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Haunted Weir Mill
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team visits Weir Mill, the oldest and most paranormally active mill in Stockport.

programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team travels to Derbyshire to investigate the New Mills Arts Theatre. This quirky little building has played host to many famous acts and world-renowned plays but has a little-known secret in that it's allegedly haunted.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Haunting of New Mills Art Theatre Part 2
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension Team is ready for act II at the New Mills Arts Theatre. With so much apparent activity happening at this unassuming theatre, the team just couldn't leave when so much more could happen.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Spirits at The Lord Eldon
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team travels to the old town of Knutsford, Cheshire to investigate the historic Lord Eldon Inn, hoping to contact the spirit of Sarah Ann Pollitt who is said to haunt the pub.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Monks and Demons at The Rutland Arms Hotel
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team journeys to Nottingham and the historic Rutland Arms Hotel. The pub and hotel have seen several centuries of change, and with that change came tragedy.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Final Session at Galleries of Justice
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team travel back in time to The Galleries of Justice in Nottingham. This was a one stop shop for justice where criminals were held awaiting trial.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Underground World Of The City of Caves
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team ventures underground to investigate the City of Caves in Nottingham.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Lost Souls Of The Tivoli Venue
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension Team travels to North Wales and the Tivoli Theatre in Flint for a night of haunting entertainment.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: The Old Glen and Milner Curse
programme.desc: The Ghost Dimension team heads to Shipley, West Yorkshire to investigate The Old Glen House Pub.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension

programme.title: Everyone Says I Love You
programme.desc: A New York girl sets her father up with a beautiful woman in a troubled marriage while her stepsister gets engaged. Starring: Woody Allen, Goldie Hawn, Julia Roberts, Edward Norton, Drew Barrymore, Natasha Lyonne, Natalie Portman.

programme.title: Air
programme.desc: A scuba diver surfaces to a world that suddenly has no breathable air. Now she must fight to find her son and family before her air tanks run out.

programme.title: Broken English
programme.desc: Nora is in her thirties, alone with job she's outgrown and a mother who constantly reminds her of it all. But after a series of disastrous dates, she unexpectedly meets Julien, a quirky Frenchman who opens her eyes to a lot more than love.

programme.title: Wheeler
programme.desc: The story of an aspiring musician from Texas who travels to Nashville to fulfill his lifelong dream of trying his hand at country music. Starring: Stephen Dorff, Kris Kristofferson, Audrey Spillman.

programme.title: Rise Of The Chupacabras

programme.title: Gracie

programme.desc: Ultracomputer Dynak X is invaded by Ming's Electronic Maggot and miniaturized Defenders must fight her war within!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Root Of Evil

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Cold War
programme.desc: Ming the Merciless develops a weather control device and plots to freeze the world solid!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Sleeper Awakes
programme.desc: A mammoth killer-robot from another galaxy has been buried right under Central City for more than ten million years Ming discovers a way to wake it up!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Revenge Of Astra

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Hall Of Wisdom

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Baby's Back in Town

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Surprise! Surprise!

programme.desc: Hunting down a fugitive known as "Bozo," Dog gets help from an unexpected source, Bozo's father-in-law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Brother's Keeper
programme.desc: Leland has a full plate of fugitives in Kona, and the whole family heads to the Big Island to help.

programme.desc: Dog visits his mother's grave for inspiration before heading out to find Frankie, a violent fugitive hiding in the jungle. The spirit of Ma Chapman seems to help when Dog finds an unusual ally; Frankie's mother.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Lost in Paradise
programme.desc: Dog lectures high school students about the dangers of drugs before going after Joseph, a dangerous fugitive who won't be easy to capture.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Coaching Day

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: To Capture One's Own
programme.desc: Dog faces a tough personal and professional situation when he must hunt down his friend, Ili, who has helped him on many busts. But now Ili's on the other side of the law, and now Dog must bring her in.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Cats & Dogs

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Destiny Love
programme.desc: Dog is in for a big surprise after he catches a fugitive named Jonaven in a sting operation.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: If You Knew Nunu
programme.desc: Dog and the team really have their hands full when they go after a tough guy named Nunu, who leads them on a chase through apartment complexes and a shopping mall before he's finally captured.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Big Island, Small Town
programme.desc: Dog has problems when he goes to a small town on the Big Island of Hawaii to track down a fugitive. In a small town, everyone knows everyone else's business, making it impossible for Dog to hunt in secret.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Jonah is Missing
programme.desc: Dog and the team search for Jonah, a violent and desperate criminal facing?20 years in jail. The trail goes stale when Dog runs into evasive family members and an angry girlfriend.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Suga On My Cuffs
programme.desc: Dog and the team go after Kandice, AKA Candy, AKA Suga, a stripper who didn't make her court appearance. They convince one of her friends to lure her to a supermarket parking lot, where Dog has an easy time fetching the fetching young thing. But then.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mothers and Daughters
